                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="42178" author="mlippert" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2009 23:56:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is a duplicate of 5401&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62836" author="wim.deblauwe" created="Fri, 28 Jan 2011 02:02:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are having the same problem in a plugin mechanism we created ourselves based on Spring. For the moment, we changed our plugins to no longer use &lt;tt&gt;@Configurable&lt;/tt&gt; anymore as a workaround. I would love to see this fixed so we can have the convenience of &lt;tt&gt;@Configurable&lt;/tt&gt; again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71103" author="wim.deblauwe" created="Sat, 8 Oct 2011 12:13:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both this issue and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-5401&quot; title=&quot;AnnotationBeanConfigurerAspect is created as a singleton and cannot be shared across multiple contexts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-5401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-5401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; are resolved as duplicate without any fix version. Does this mean that the issue will not be solved at all ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71107" author="cbeams" created="Sat, 8 Oct 2011 16:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, that was actually a mistake.  I meant to slate one of these issues for a backlog, but ended up resolving them both as duplicates of each other in the end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="92517" author="ahoehma" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 13:40:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any progress in this direction???&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="92530" author="tcharl" created="Tue, 6 Aug 2013 23:45:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To what I know Spring is not OSGI anymore (in 3.2, Manifests aren&apos;t generated anymore).&lt;br/&gt;
You can try Gemini or Aries projects to have DI (PAX-CDI for annotations), and Virgo to have a nice Configurable annotation support.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to have a full Spring support for OSGI out of the box, but for the time I&apos;m following this, my hope is decreasing from day to day...   &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
